<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-11-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-11-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1035" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1035">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/19885</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">French Consul, Mazatlan</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-11-17">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 17, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department informed several American citizens left Parral, Chihuahua, on
                            November 3, for Culiacan. These Americans were threatened by bandits and
                            could not come out by way of border. They are traveling on
                            horseback.</p>
                        <p>Please communicate with Culiacan and endeavor ascertain whether said
                            Americans have arrived there, and if not, request appropriate
                            authorities to assist you in locating Americans in question. Kindly keep
                            Department informed of developments.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>